  <span id="freeText14799199508144358248" style="display:none">For my full review and thoughts on the story, characters and ending completely spoiler free please visit my blog <a href="http://www.lousbookstuff.com/2021/01/04/petals-on-the-wind-by-virginia-andrews-review-dollanganger-book-2/" rel="nofollow noopener">here</a><br /><br /><br />STORY--<br />The children have escaped the attic and are now running toward a new life in Florida. This second book in the series follows Cathy, Chris and Carrie as they try to rebuild their lives, achieve their ambitions and plot revenge.<br /><br />OVERALL--<br />I didn't like it as much as Flowers in the Attic but I still found it to be a thrilling read right up until the end where it kind of fell off a cliff for me. I'll still give it 4 stars really I would say it's a rounded up 3.5</span>
